The maintenance actions will be scheduled to occur at the minimum of the intervale from the last performance and the phase from the next scheduled time of the phase maintenance requirement. For example, in a four phase 200hr cycle, there will be four maintenance checks (A1 through A4). Each will have an intervale of 200 hours and a phase intervale of 50 hrs. Maintenance Requirement A2 will have phase maintenance requirement of A1 and a phase intervale of 50 hours.
